  "title": "Aureline companion remote-preview, session-handoff, light-remote-edit, and scoped collaboration-follow continuity surfaces",
  "description": "Export-safe packet for the companion surfaces that remotely preview and hand off an active desktop session, perform a single bounded light remote edit, and follow a collaborator within a host-revocable shared scope. It projects three surfaces — remote-preview-handoff, light-remote-edit, and collaboration-follow — each inheriting qualification from a frozen M5 companion-matrix lane, and gives every item an exact desktop handoff. Bounded read/write scope: remote-preview-handoff and collaboration-follow are read-only; only the light-remote-edit surface may write, and only via a host-approved relay. Scoped collaboration-follow continuity: collaboration-follow is confined to a host-revocable shared scope, never an unbounded view. Local-core continuity: a remote preview is a read-only projection, a session handoff never strands user-owned local work, and the local core stays authoritative. Stale-state honesty: every item carries a freshness state, stale or unknown freshness is always labeled, and a degraded item is never shown as live. Degraded state (relay unavailable, stale proof, inactive host, narrowed trust, revoked collaboration scope, narrowed upstream lane, unresolved handoff, downgraded freshness) is labeled rather than hidden. Credential bodies, raw provider payloads, and raw session, edit, or collaboration bodies never cross this boundary.",
